beer_brewer_name: Magic Hat Brewing Company (North American Breweries)
review_blob: I am a fan, nice dark and moderatly hoppy at the front. nice caramelized finish.
A good beer that can be found pretty much anywhere. The 25oz keg cans are pretty neat, keeps alot of beer cold without fridge trips! Id like to try this one on draft. Refreshing on a hot day.

Not a bad stout! Nice deep chocolaty flavour, though contrary to other reviews, I found this one a little on the overcarbonated side, with not quite enough body for the style. Still quite drinkable, but definatly lacking.
Not reccomended. The only beer option at a rather good indian food place. Reminded me of stella artois, only in a bad way. A too sweet, to watery lager.

This is definatly the most intruiging beer I have yet sampled. Amazing on draft, and quite good bottle to glass. Im thinking of heading down to the brewery and picking up a 1/5 keg for $60. Well worth it.
Theres just something really great about this beer. Drinks like water, if youre into throwing them back, even better on draft, if you can find it.
